The paper discusses the development and use of a robotic body surrogate to assist people with profound motor deficits in performing physical tasks. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of augmented reality and machine learning algorithms to control the robot suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the study involves collecting and analyzing data, which could be related to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
